<section id="problem-statement" class="content-section">
  <div class="section-container">

    <!-- Title -->
    <h2 class="section-heading">
      Sensor-to-Decision Bottleneck in Agentic AI Robots
    </h2>

    <!-- Highlighted Intro Box -->
    <div class="intro-box">
      <p>
        Agentic AI robots can show low per-frame latency and high perception accuracy, yet still fail when decisions are made from <strong>stale sensor evidence</strong>. In real deployment, redundant, sparse, and vibration-distorted camera/LiDAR streams consume onboard compute, create queues, and delay decision-relevant observations.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Key Problems -->
    <!-- Item 1 -->
    <div class="highlight-item">
      <div class="highlight-icon">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path d="M3 12h18M3 6h18M3 18h18"/>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <div class="highlight-content">
        <h4>Stale Decision Inputs</h4>
        <p>
          Accurate perception becomes unsafe when queued frames or scans reach the planner too late for the current scene.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Item 2 -->
    <div class="highlight-item">
      <div class="highlight-icon">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/>
          <path d="M12 7v5l3 3"/>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <div class="highlight-content">
        <h4>Low-Value Stream Overload</h4>
        <p>
          Near-duplicate frames, sparse regions, and vibration-amplified artifacts waste compute, memory, and I/O without improving decisions.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Item 3 -->
    <div class="highlight-item">
      <div class="highlight-icon">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <polyline points="4 17 10 11 13 14 20 7"/>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <div class="highlight-content">
        <h4>Delayed Critical Evidence</h4>
        <p>
          Safety-relevant observations such as pedestrians, vehicles, occlusions, or rough-terrain changes may arrive after the robot has already planned.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Bridge -->
    <div class="bridge-text">
      <p>
        <strong>Sense-Think-Act</strong> addresses this bottleneck by treating real-time robustness as a <strong>decision-time freshness objective</strong>. It adaptively drops, reduces, or fully processes camera frames and LiDAR scans using visual/geometric change, cached semantic risk cues, runtime pressure, and safety overrides, while retaining compact failure-aligned evidence for continual improvement.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>



<section id="image-showcase" class="content-section">
  <div class="section-container">

    <!-- Title -->
    <h2 class="section-heading">Failure Case: Stale Perception Under Challenging Conditions</h2>

    <!-- Highlighted Intro Box -->
    <div class="problem-intro-box">

      <p class="section-intro">
        Under vibration, blur, noise, and uneven terrain, <strong>redundant or distorted sensor streams</strong> can delay informative evidence. The robot may then act on <strong>stale perception</strong>, causing missed detections and weaker planning reliability.
      </p>

      <p class="group-description">
        The left illustrates stale perception under challenging deployment conditions, while the right shows how adaptive stream refinement helps preserve fresher, decision-relevant sensing.
      </p>

    </div>

    <!-- Comparison -->
    <div class="image-pair">

      <!-- BEFORE -->
      <div class="image-card">
        <iframe 
          src="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1R2sQOs8LKBlH2kDEpd74cFOKFQpBsW0X/preview"
          allow="autoplay"
          title="Failure video">
        </iframe>

        <p class="image-label">Stale Perception</p>
      </div>

      <!-- AFTER -->
      <div class="image-card">
        <img 
          src="https://drive.google.com/thumbnail?id=1RfFGE0oFWyu_Y5CMWwD_ZAvSUXCY-Ycw&sz=w1000"
          alt="Adaptive sensing with fresher evidence"
        />

        <p class="image-label">Fresh Adaptive Sensing</p>
      </div>

    </div>

  </div>
</section>



<section id="research-questions" class="content-section">
  <div class="section-container">

    <h2 class="section-heading">Research Questions</h2>

    <div class="research-questions-box">

      <!-- RQ1 -->
      <div class="question-item">
        <div class="question-badge">1</div>
        <div class="question-content">
          <h4>Decision-Time Freshness</h4>
          <p>
            How can we maximize <strong>decision-time freshness</strong> under limited compute by adaptively filtering and refining camera/LiDAR streams?
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- RQ2 -->
      <div class="question-item">
        <div class="question-badge">2</div>
        <div class="question-content">
          <h4>Failure-Driven Improvement</h4>
          <p>
            What <strong>minimal multimodal evidence</strong> should be retained to support efficient model improvement under deployment shift?
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

  </div>
</section>

